 ('737', '842', 'en_us', 'Amahl and the Night Visitors and John Rutter’s Dancing Day', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p>Join us this Friday, December 15, for a fully staged and costumed production of Menotti’s beloved opera, with the Transfiguration Boys and Girls Choirs and Camerata, a full orchestra, plus John Rutter’s <em>Dancing Day</em>. Luciano Pantano, Amahl; Jodi Karem, The Mother; Ben Thomas, Kaspar, Jake Ingbar, Melchior; Charles Brown, Balthazar. Katie Andrews, harp. “To hear and see the chorus, children and adults is to see a rainbow of nationalities united by music – perhaps the greatest unifying force in the world today!” — <em>The Brooklyn Discovery </em><br /></p>\n<p><em>General Admission: $35 <br /></em><em> Seniors and students: $25<br /> Tickets can be purchased online <a href=\"https://www.artful.ly/the-church-of-the-transfiguration\"><strong>here</strong></a>.  </em></p>\n<p><br /></p>', '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '1', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-10-30 17:37:59', '2018-01-03 14:16:37', 'a0ffe32f-7eee-4674-97c9-fee84ca92795'),
 ('738', '843', 'en_us', 'Concert Series', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><em>Tickets: $30 / $15 for students and seniors</em><br />The Quartet closes out 2017 with the first three works from Haydn\'s Op. 17, composed in 1771. These refreshing,  rarely played gems delight with surprising harmonies, lush expression, quirky, irregular phrase lengths, and Haydn\'s ever-present wit.</p>', '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '0', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', '<p>Franz Joseph Haydn:&nbsp; Quartets Op. 17</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2017-10-31 17:48:50', '2017-12-13 20:59:13', '4ef9a689-587e-4153-8e85-609c6cbf66e0'),
