 ('121', '234', '7', '1', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Brief History\",\"slug\":\"our-history\",\"postDate\":1504211220,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"236\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>The Civil War<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The parish had only been established for a few years, when the Civil War broke out. &nbsp;During this time, the church was a stop on the Underground Railroad, sheltering escaped slaves on their journey north. It was a place of refuge for African Americans during the New York Draft Riots of 1863&mdash;three days of lawlessness, destruction, bloodshed, and lynchings.<\\/p><h2>The Nickname<\\/h2><p>A few days before Christmas in 1890, Joseph Jefferson, an actor renowned for his portrayal of Rip Van Winkle, approached the rector of the now-defunct Church of the Atonement to request a funeral for his friend and fellow actor, George Holland. &nbsp;Upon learning that the deceased was an actor, the rector refused to hold a funeral for the man in his church. &nbsp;Joseph Jefferson persisted, and asked if there was a church in the area that would hold services for his friend. &nbsp;The rector said, \\u201cI believe there is a little church around the corner where it might be done.\\u201d &nbsp;Jefferson replied,&nbsp;<\\/p><blockquote>\\u201cThen I say to you, sir, God bless the little church around the corner.\\u201d<\\/blockquote>\"}}},\"11\":[\"235\"],\"12\":\"<blockquote>Church of the Transfiguration parish was founded in 1848. &nbsp;The building itself dates from 1850; it was made a national landmark in 1973. &nbsp;The founder, the Rev. Dr. George Hendric Houghton wanted to build a church that would serve the needs of the poor and marginalized, and would welcome all regardless of race, class or background.<\\/blockquote>\",\"27\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-04 20:51:38', '2017-09-04 20:51:38', '88ca2061-8b85-4ebd-be90-86faac1ad8fe'),
