r\\\">Convention Resolution 2012-A054<\\/a>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The words of this liturgy give me the hope that, one day, we will be reunited with our animal companions under the eternal care of God. Although we cannot have absolute certainty about this, we can hope that God\\u2019s love for all creation is so strong that it will overcome the pain of&nbsp;separation and death.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>In my own view, heaven would not be, as the catechism in the Book of Common Prayer puts it, \\u201ceternal life in our enjoyment of God\\u201d without the presence of our beloved animal companions. See <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.episcopalchurch.org\\/library\\/glossary\\/heaven\\\">BCP 862<\\/a>. And so, I fervently hope that pets do in fact go to heaven.<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"206\"],\"26\":\"Fr. Patrick S. Cheng\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-09-30 18:02:33', '2017-09-30 18:02:33', '48e9c760-34cc-4c4d-b28c-90d7cfb5f850'),
