his time, holding a mask and dressed in Greco-Roman costume.&nbsp; (Edwin Booth was the brother of the notorious John Wilkes Booth, President Lincoln\\u2019s assassin.) The window was given in his memory in 1898 by members of the Players Club, which he founded.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>And a few steps away, near the chancel on the northeast side of the nave, stands Richard Upjohn\\u2019s beautiful and intricate brass filigree pulpit.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"122\":{\"type\":\"figure\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"216\"],\"altAttribute\":\"Richard Upjohn\\u2019s beautiful and intricate brass filigree pulpit\",\"caption\":\"<p>Richard Upjohn\\u2019s beautiful and intricate brass filigree pulpit<\\/p>\",\"enlarge\":\"1\",\"orientation\":\"horizontal\"}},\"126\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>How fortunate we are to have works by all three of these masters under the roof of the \\u201cLittle Church\\u201d.&nbsp; I will give thanks when December 16<sup>th<\\/sup>&nbsp;rolls around.<\\/p>\"}},\"218\":{\"type\":\"footnote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p><em><em>Holy Women, Holy Men<\\/em>: Celebrating the Saints<\\/em> by Church Publishing Incorporated<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"205\"],\"26\":\"Mary Jane Gocher\",\"27\":\"Corey Schneider\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-01 00:12:25', '2017-10-01 00:12:25', '39edcb2d-a281-4226-aff4-0e76f4986990'),
 ('239', '221', '9', '1', 'en_us', '14', '', '{\"typeId\":\"9\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"The Garden\",\"slug\":\"the-garden\",\"postDate\":1506781320,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"28\":{\"224\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>Besides being an oasis of rest and comfort for one and all, the garden provides a small but significant ecological benefit for everyone. The 4,230 square feet of plants, shrubs and trees offset carbon emissions, and the peace and quiet of the garden offer relief from the city\\u2019s noise pollution.&nbsp;<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Birds stop by to dip their beaks in the fountain. During the week, it\\u2019s a popular lunch spot for people who work in the neighborhood, and on Sundays in warm weather, it\\u2019s the site of coffee&nbsp;hour. This past summer, the garden was enhanced with the generous gift of an apple tree from frequent visitors to the church from the Como Hotel group. This tree replaces one that was lost during Hurricane Sandy. Please stop by if you\\u2019re in the neighborhood. You will always be welcome&nbsp;here.<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"223\"],\"26\":\"Mary Jane Gocher\",\"27\":\"Ahron R. Foster Photography\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-01 00:12:35', '2017-10-01 00:12:35', 'f475c7bb-d0da-40ef-8efe-01a6e0d26eb9'),
