:\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"626\"],\"altAttribute\":\"\",\"caption\":\"\",\"credit\":\"\",\"enlarge\":\"\",\"orientation\":\"horizontal\"}},\"653\":{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<h2>Colors<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Colors used in the Transfiguration logo show the parish\\u2019s reverence for the love of God and his Divine majesty. Many of the colors used in the logo are also representative of seasons throughout the liturgical year.<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><li><strong>Gold<\\/strong> is used throughout the logo to outline each distinct shape. Gold is the emblem of the sun and of divinity.<\\/li><li>The color <strong>Red<\\/strong> in the corners of the logo represents fire and blood, especially blood of martyred saints.<\\/li><li>The color of the perfect Circle representing the infinity of God is <strong>Purple<\\/strong>, representing imperial power and God\\u2019s majesty.<\\/li><li>The Quatrefoil is colored <strong>Blue<\\/strong>. Blue, the color of sky, symbolizes Heaven and heavenly love. Blue is the color of truth.<\\/li><li>The <strong>Green<\\/strong> of the Triangle represents life, especially vegetation and spring, which reminds us of the triumph of spring over winter, of life over death.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"647\":{\"type\":\"footnote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>The Mission Statement of Transfiguration is: The Church of the Transfiguration is a&nbsp;community committed to faith in action (Fides Opera), embracing all who seek God\\u2019s&nbsp;inclusive love.<\\/p>\"}}},\"25\":[\"609\"],\"26\":\"Gary Norcross\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-01 12:11:48', '2017-10-01 12:11:48', 'f4f52fbf-16d2-4c39-9e37-db0b2ca0c33e'),
 ('261', '244', '10', '655', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Worship Schedule\",\"slug\":\"worship-schedule\",\"postDate\":1504260780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"3\":\"\",\"13\":{\"245\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>At the center of our worship is emphasis on both Word and Table. Little Church clergy are considered <a href=\\\"#\\\">excellent preachers<\\/a>&nbsp;who connect lectionary readings with Biblical context and current challenges with a smattering of personal stories and humor. Transfiguration acolytes do an extraordinary job in ensuring the Eucharist is celebrated with majesty and dignity, and the authentic expertise of <a href=\\\"#\\\">our choirs<\\/a>&nbsp;draws worshippers closer to the love of Jesus Christ through some of the most beloved hymns of the Church.&nbsp;Below is the current worship schedule. Please consider joining us!<\\/p>\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"generalSection\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"text\":\"<p>PREACHING AND CELEBRANT SCHEDULE<\\/p><p><strong>October 8, 2017<br><\\/strong>Celebrant: &nbsp;<br>Preacher:<\\/p><p><b>October 15, 2017<\\/b><br>Celebrant: &nbsp;<br>Preacher:<br><\\/p><p><b>October 22, 2017<\\/b><br>Celebrant: &nbsp;<br>Preacher:<\\/p><p><b>October 29, 2017<\\/b><br>Celebrant: &nbsp;<br>Preacher:<br><\\/p>\"}}},\"11\":[\"243\"],\"12\":\"<p>The cornerstone of Transfiguration\\u2019s spirituality is how we express and demonstrate God\\u2019s inclusive love through liturgy, music and worship. As an Anglo-Catholic parish, Transfiguration honors traditional liturgy with a full complement of meaningful preaching and music.<\\/p>\",\"27\":\"\",\"70\":\"\"}}', '2017-10-03 22:23:08', '2017-10-03 22:23:08', 'b4269d6c-25ae-45ce-8911-e819accd51e0'),
