 ('76', 'field', '1', 'en_us', ' the rev deacon ian betts was born and raised in canada to a roman catholic mother and a protestant father so he had the best of both worlds as far as his religious backgrounds are concerned he later discovered that his father s family was not only protestant but anglican so ultimately he has come back home to the anglican communion ian immigrated to the us in 1984 for a year to finish his dance training at the martha graham school of contemporary dance he ended up staying to finish his dance education at the school for another 3 years and then began his performing career with one of his graham teachers pearl lang ian danced for pearl for 17 years until she s closed her company in 1985 through a friend ian discovered the episcopal church of the good shepherd on east 31st st after 9 years into his life at the parish the diaconate was brought to the diocese of new york by bishop richard grein and it became clear to him that he was called to the diaconate his rector at the time highly recommended that he pursue this calling and in 1998 he was ordained deacon in 2002 ian s rector retired so he moved to the cathedral of saint john the divine for 8 years when that term ended bishop andrew st john invited ian to join transfiguration where he is now celebrating 8 years at this wonderful parish ian supports his ministry and life by working at a mid town law firm as an administrative assistant he has been working with lawyers since 1985 and is grateful for their support of his extracurricular activities for over 32 years '),
