 ('270', 'field', '14', 'en_us', ' the theatre to this day the church maintains close ties with the theatre it has served as the national headquarters of the episcopal actors guild since its founding in 1923 by the third rector the dr randolph ray weddings our historic buildings and lovely garden have drawn couples from all over the world to be married here these couples are members of the little family and many have stayed in touch with us over the years continuing its long tradition of inclusiveness the little church is proud to have celebrated the first same sex wedding in the diocese of new york in july 2012 and has performed several more since the formal rite of blessing of a lifelong covenant was adopted by the general convention we invite you to stop by for a visit join us in worship or simply contact us for more information '),
